Three men are due to appear at the Emanguzi Magistrate s Court following the discovery in their possession of heroin worth R104m on Monday.Members of the Pretoria Crime Intelligence had been gathering information about a vehicle which was due to enter the country through the Kosi Bay Port of Entry with drugs.The Task Team at the port of entry was immediately activated. The described vehicle was stopped and taken to a nearby police station for &#8220;a thorough search&#8221;.Several bags of drugs allegedly fetched from Mozambique were found concealed inside a make-shift compartment underneath the vehicle.A 27-year-old man was immediately arrested which led to intensive investigations being conducted which led the Hawks to Gauteng where two suspects &#8211; age 24 and 29 years &#8211; were arrested.During their arrest police also found an amount of R50 000-00 in cash.-TNA Reporter 